comment: This class prepared me so well for a further courses. I took the next cs course and the professor decided to give a test day one. If it weren't for Dr. Bloch I wouldn't have done well at all. Amazing professor.
Amazing. The only professor to ever make me feel prepared for the actual job world so far at adelphi.
Gigantic step above professor like siegfried. This man actually knows his stuff unlike the previously mentioned.

Hands down a great example of what not only a computer science professor should be like but what any professor should be. Nice guy all around and is extremely helpful.sometimes he doesn't comes prepared with notes and this is usually a time for the class to talk about anything they're confused on. Homework assignments are hard but you learn a lot

This course was very challenging and he is a tough professor but by far the most I have learned from any one of the computer science professors. If you want your moneys worth in tuition I suggest taking a class with him and not anyone else.
He is a helpful professor, but computer programs are difficult for
Worst porfessor Ever never take him!

Very nice man he helps you when you ask for it but can sometimes be cryptic with his answers. If you're expecting an easy A don't come to this class because his work load is a lot! Very difficult too. Unless you're in love with programming i'd suggest you take another elective class.

Google will be your best friend and pretty much only lifeline. His office hours stand as him just insulting your intelligence and don't help. If I could avoid classes with him I would. Possibly transferring.

This man is a failure to Adelphi. The computer science department is failing because of him. He piles on homework every week, to a point where students cannot handle it. He does not teach anything but an old, used language. He cannot teach and is incredibly unhelpful.  Do not hurt your GPA by taking his class.

This man cannot teach for his life. I've talked to other majors and they all have said he has become worse over the years. Most of the people in my class switched to different majors after this class. DO NOT TAKE HIM HE IS HORRIBLE! There is a coalition trying to remove him from the university.

I took the class as an elective. BIG MISTAKE. I'm pretty good with computers and I was lost from day one. Tried to get help and he just confused me more. The man is definetly smart, but too much time behind the computer has left him with no people skills and an inability to reach his students.

hes a bit of a weird guy, I never really understood him. If you ask him for help he doesnt really give you the answer right there, he wants you to figure it out. Better off never asking him since you can find the answers somewhere else.

Definitely the most challenging CS professor at AU. He gives a lot of work and he expects a lot of effort in return. Biggest mistakes you can make: not participating in class and not seeking extra help. He really will help you a lot during office hours. If he sees that you don't care enough to ask for guidance, your grade will reflect that.

At first I said, "Oh no!", I am going to fail this class!  Well, that was not the case!  Professor Bloch cares a lot about his students and he is always available for extra help!  You can e-mail him and within an hour he will have answered you!  Expect to get a lot of work and spend a lot of time working on it, but it will be worth it!

DEFINATELY DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS IF YOU DON"T KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT COMPUTERS!! He's the most confusing tacher, not very nice, expects you to get everything, hard assignments, brilliant person just not a great professor. If you want to take it for a challenge, go for it otherwise take a different class!!
He is very knowledgeable, helpful and patient. the lecture was well orgonized.

Without a doubt the hardest teacher I have EVER had.  But you can't help but learn something in his class.  He isn't always the clearest since he knows what he's talking about and can't always translate that well for students but he's immensely helpful and would go out of his way in explaining stuff till you understand.  Great but hard as hell.

worst teacher ever, DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS!!!!!!! doesnt teach his students anything but expects us to know everything. The homework is terribly hard and impossible for an entry level course. Someone please remind him this is Adelphi and not Harvard.

so i have to take this guy for the hardest class imaginable to graduate.....COMPLEXITY!!! this scares the **** out of me since takeing a class with this guy is like mission immpossible. i think the other proffessors would fail his intro level courses...... pray for me.

Yes, he makes his classes difficult. Yes, he expects you to know a LOT. Yes, he expects you to RTFM. On the flipside: yes, *he* knows a *LOT*. Yes, he teaches rather well imho. Yes, he curves. He might be the toughest prof at AU by far, but what doesn't kill you makes you stronger.

Very good Prof, but maybe the toughest.Coz other clss are a lot easier, lots of ppl dont expct it.He try to keep up the stndrd a bit to be comparable to other Univ, so he goes trough the material prty fast.Need to read the asgnmnts to undrstnd him,he hlp u if u try.Lots of work,but it'll get u ready
DESPICABLE AND SPITS A WHOLE LOT!!!!!!!!!!!  AVOID AT ALL COSTS!!!!!!!

Doesn't teach a thing.  Talks about current events and then expects you to know the material.  Never hands anything back on time (I still haven't recieved my research paper and I handed it in 3 months ago) Teaches Math in Computer class
Should a professor really refer to his students as idiots????  NO!!!!!

He is the worst teacher i ever had. Very unhelpful. he does not teach you anything but expects you to know EVERYTHING. He is belittling and BORING. He should stick to just teaching math, better yet he shouldn't be teaching at all!
This teacher is an obvious ****.  He especially hates Mexicans.

i suggest you change your course if you have this guy...he is not a good teacher at all and his hw's are incredibly forever...it can take up about 6 straight hrs to do 1 homework
Stick with Siegfried!
Prof. Bloch is a good  teacher and if you disagree do yourself a favor and take chen and then let me know what you think of Dr. bloch becuase youll think hes a miracle worker compared to her!

this class is like a waste of time. we do nothing that helps us to learn.  he shouldnt teach this class ever and shaving doesnt hurt either

one of the many social justice warriors teaching in the department. more interested in promoting her partisan agenda than examining reality and facts. as long as you go along, you'll do fine. challenge her at your own peril...
I love Lake! Shes very caring and easy to talk to! Great professor!
Best professor on campus!

Professor Lake is the BEST! She is there for you inside and outside of class. She is the best advisor I ever had. She comments a lot on papers but is a fair grader. Read the textbook and you can know what is important in her lectures! I would strongly advise taking her.

She is very knowledgable and passionate about the subject. She does tend to go on tangents and she doesn't follow powerpoints but the tangents are always relevant to the material. Her assignments and papers are easy. She gives thorough outlines of both the midterm and final.

Worst class I have ever taken. Terribly taught, redundant lectures, very opinionated and makes you feel like you're in economics. Rather than learning about criminals and criminal behavior, you learn about social justice and why she is 100% right about her own opinions. Tell her what she wants to hear, you're fine. Wanna argue otherwise? Be smart
Love her! Great professor, knows her stuff!
Prof Lake is THE BEST!!! she cares about her students, and her Lectures are AMAZING!! if you really want to learn, take her courses.

Terrible teacher. All she cares about is spreading her political views. She doesn't cover the material in class that is required for the midterm and the final. Unless you want to hear about her political views and not the class material DON'T TAKE HER!!!

Im taking an online class with her and she is incredible, I wish I could take more classes with her in person. She is just so passionate about the subject and it encourages you to  study more, because it gets really interesting.   She also loves Homeland which is my fav show.

She is a nice person. Seems to be passionate about the topic. However, I think I joined her at a bad time. Entire class was more on the Presidential debate than the actual topic or material we were reading or discussing.  The lectures were all over the place. Hard to keep up as to what she wanted me to understand from the content vs. her lectures.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--Participation matters

comment: I loved this professor! Took her for Minority Groups in America.  She is so passionate about the subject. Loved the class---

Took Social Problems by Lakie, AWESOME Professor.  She really makes you think.  She goes over a lot of different topics throughout the course. She really opens your mind to the world around you.  She is compassionate about her work and her beliefs. Take this class if you want to learn. She's helpful and attentive to her students. Easy class.

Steph is a very close friend, and I will never forget her classes. She is the best teacher I've ever had. Yes, she goes off on tangents, but they're always fun and full of real-world information. Take her class, you will not be sorry. FYI I've never read a single one of the textbooks. Just be intelligent & listen to her and you'll get an A.

Nice professor but a LARGE amount of work for a 200 level class. Expect to read the textbook every week. To start: midterm and final with multiple choice questions and essays. Then 2 book reviews (each book approx 200pgs) with a paper on each book(each paper approx 6-7 pgs). Also required to attend at least 3 outside events with a 1 page write-up.

What can i say about Lakiee, she is the best, There is no doubt about it that Adelphi will be no where without her. Her enthusiam and energy and care she has for her students is exemplorly love you lakieeeee
Prof. Lake is the best professor i have ever had at adelphi. She is not only inspiring but extremely helpful and truly cares about the future of her students. SHES THE BEST!!

Professor lake is one of the best professors i have ever had she is so helpful and sweet and extremely funny and she is generally concerned with her students i have sick and she sent me the sweetest email and i love her personal stories and the stories about her cat
There is no other like prof. lake. Stephanie brings to life the real world and everything you really want to know.
Prof. Lake is a very involved citizen and truely cares about the outcome of her students in class and outside of class.  She gives herself to her profession and her students.

To "Crim246"-Prof. Lake, lazy?!?! That is an unsubstantiated statement. Maybe U were not paying attention. Prof. Lake is one of the few professors that takes great pride in teaching social sci. and politicization.  She supplies a plethora of information that one is forced 2 critically think about the environment in which we live in. Academia wuld s
big on political agenda...

This professor is lazy, she doesn't get through the material she feels that she must and them puts the material she didn't get to cover on the test. The midterm was outrageous. All she does is prosthelytize regarding her liberal agenda. It should be clear that a professor's political views have no place in the classroom. For shame!

Great professor.  Midterm and Final are multiple choice and essay but she gives you the essays prior so you can prepare.  Knows what she is talking about and her class is fun.  2 book reviews, not to hard, but is a fair grader.  If you show up to class and hand in everything expect a good grade.

I'm taking sociology classes to fill up stuff for my major: She's one of the only professors in sociology who's welcoming to everyone, not just 'favorites'. She cares about students, she's insightful (albeit very crazed), and not jaded or bitter like the rest of the Soc. Department seems. She's awesome... Take her classes.

OMG this teacher is the funniest, most bubbly, most interesting teacher I have ever had in my academic career so far.  She incorporates her funny and weird personal life into teacher which makes it even funnier.....basement dweller, sashsquatch, inaugural ball, nambla...god the list goes on and on....love u prof lake

Wonderful Prof who knows what she's teaching and obviously loves it-she goes off on tangents but there interesting and funny..she's great..I wish I had more than one more semester at adelphi but i'm taking another class with her next semester- she makes you work but i didn't mind-it was well worth it-she will make you learn in a fun way-she cares

Prolly the best freaking professor ever...she's hilarious with her lovely tangents but her teaching is amazing....i have taken a class with her before and i did very well....def recommend taking a class with professor lake!!!
I MISS PROFESSOR LAKE!!! BARBIES, DIET COKE, and MR. WINKLE!!!

She is sooo freakin awesome. Great teacher. And cute too!
I <3 her. She is an amazing prof. Take any class with her because I said so. Yea she's great.
